args: (Ugh! They're both perfectly in sync with\neach other—and they're not holding back!)
They're on a completely different level\nfrom us. What do we even do here?
Please just stop this!\nI don't want to fight another apostle!
Gah! Her strength really is absurd.\nGood thing I brought Ramiel.\nNo way I'd be able to take her alone.
You don't need to tell me twice!
Hey, she's getting away! AFTER HER!
What do you think you're doing?!
Oh, I am terribly sorry. You were making\nsuch a small contribution to the battle\nthat I mistook you for a wall.
Grrr... So you're trying to tell me that was\nan accident?
'Course it was. But I'd hurry after them\nif I were you—you're gonna lose them.
Bah. The bishop will be hearing of this!
Not yet! But she can't have gone far!
Phew... I finally lost them.\nBut at this rate, it's only a\nmatter of time before—
You're found? Well, searching for things\nIS my specialty.
Why are you so determined, Nevin?!
You must KNOW I'm not the murderer!
I told you—because I have my orders,\nand to us apostles, orders are absolute.
Surely he won't follow me this far.
Don't count on that.\nI know how you think.
How did you get here first?!\nI have to put some space between us!
(There's nowhere for me to run.\nDid they lure me here on purpose?\nWas this their plan all along?)
Then I can't afford to hold back!
Save it. Don't make this harder than it\nneeds to be after I went to the effort of\nshaking off those pesky Templars.
I'm tired enough from having to\nrun around in the dark like this.\nI just wanna get this over with.
I don't have time to explain this in a way\nthat'll make sense to you, so I'll cut right\nto the chase.
Pursuing you is an official mission.\nIf you want those orders revoked,\nyou'll need to prove your innocence.
Normally, there'd be physical evidence in\nand around the church where the crime\ntook place, but I'm guessing that's gone.
And if clues're a no-go, all that's left is\ngetting caught and awaiting your fate.
That doesn't leave me with many options...
I have a message for you from Raphael.
＂Whenever you feel like cowardice is going\nto get the better of you, count on me and\nyour friends, like I depend on you.＂
I heard this from Sandalphon rather than\nRaphael herself, mind you.
But if you were ordered to hunt me down,\nthat means I can't depend on apostles OR\nangels.
Bingo. Everyone has friends, but you're\nnot going to find what you need here.
Stop talking to our target and finish her!

Leave the Church side of things to me,
and go find someone on the outside who
can help you. May we next meet in the
arms of the Goddess herself.
What an explosion! Even a mass of muscle\nlike her couldn't survive a fall like that.

Heh. The apostles really are a bunch of
monsters if they're able to turn on their
own at the drop of a hat when the mission
demands it.
Hey! What do you think you're doing?!
Don't you need to report to the bishop?\nWe're leaving.
Hmph. I don't need YOU to tell me that!
*sigh* I dread to think how Raphael will\nreact when she finds out about this.
